> Get your freekeh on! This supergrain, which is a type of wheat, is definitely worth vibing to because it packs plenty of healthful fiber and protein. Plus, it's got an amazing flavor that's a bit earthy and smoky. In this recipe, it's joined by even more powerhouse ingredients, like pistachios, feta cheese, and roasted bell peppers and carrots with harissa. Now that's the deal-io.

== Roasted Veggies ==

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of generously salted water to a boil. Peel @carrots{3} and halve lengthwise, then slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve, core, and seed @bell pepper{1}, then cut into ½-inch-wide strips. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Chop @parsley{¼%ounce}. Zest @lemon{1}, then halve; squeeze juice into a #small bowl{}.

Toss bell pepper and carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}, a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}, and @harissa powder{1-2%tsp}, depending on how much spice you like. Roast in oven until tender, about ~{20%minutes}.

== Freekeh ==

Once water is boiling, add @freekeh{½%cup} to #pot{}. Boil until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Drain and return freekeh to pot.

== Shallot and Pistachios ==

Place shallot in another small bowl with 1 TBSP lemon juice, a pinch of salt, and @sugar{1%tsp}. Toss to coat. Set aside to marinate. Place @pistachios{1%ounce}, a drizzle of olive oil, and half the @za'atar spice{1%tsp} in a #small pan{}. Place pan over medium-high heat and toast pistachios, tossing frequently, until aromatic and a warm golden-brown shade, about ~{5%minutes}.

== Dressing and Feta Sauce ==

Mix lemon zest, a large pinch of salt, and 2 TBSP olive oil with remaining lemon juice in #bowl{}. In another small bowl, stir together @yogurt{4%ounce}, @feta cheese{½%cup}, and remaining za'atar. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture has a consistency that's thick and creamy but not stiff.

== Assembly ==

Pour lemon dressing over freekeh in pot and stir to coat. Divide between plates, then arrange veggies on top. Dollop with feta sauce. Garnish with shallot, pistachios, and parsley.